eter on. "188.8" flashes in the centre of the display window, then a dash (-), then the last temperature taken and then three dashes (- - - ) and a flashing "F" in the upper right corner.</label><item><label>Done</label><value>done</value></item><item><label>Not Done</label><value>not</value></item></select1><select1 appearance="list-nolabel" ref="/data/intro/step3"><label>Holds the thermometer upwards and places the shinning tip under the baby's arm at the apex of the axilla, parallel to the lateral wall of the chest of the baby.</label><item><label>Done</label><value>done</value></item><item><label>Not Done</label><value>not</value></item></select1><select1 appearance="list-nolabel" ref="/data/intro/step4"><label>There will be a beep sound every 4 seconds while the thermometer is recording the temperature. When she hears 3 short beeps, looks at the display. When "F" stops flashing and the number stops changing, removes the thermometer.</label><item><label>Done</label><value>done</value></item><item><label>Not Done</label><value>not</value></item></select1><select1 appearance="list-nolabel" ref="/data/intro/step5"><label>Reads the number in the display window. Records the temperature reading on the form.</label><item><label>Done</label><value>done</value></item><item><label>Not Done</label><value>not</value></item></select1><select1 appearance="list-nolabel" ref="/data/intro/step6"><label>Turns the thermometer off by pushing the pink button one time.</label><item><label>Done</label><value>done</value></item><item><label>Not Done</label><value>not</value></item></select1><select1 appearance="list-nolabel" ref="/data/intro/step7"><label>Cleans the shinning tip of the thermometer with a cotton ball soaked in spirit and places thermometer back in its storage.</label><item><label>Done</label><value>done</value></item><item><label>Not Done</label><value>not</value></item></select1></group></h:body></h:html>